BUSINESS CONTEXT — READ THIS FIRST
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The chemist shop also offers printing services to the local 
neighbourhood. Customers can:
  — Upload a PDF, DOCX, JPG, or PNG from their phone
  — Choose print settings (B&W or colour, single/double side, 
    number of copies, paper size A4/A3/Letter)
  — Pay online (Razorpay UPI/card) before printing
  — Receive a unique 6-character alphanumeric pickup code (e.g. PRN-4K7X)
  — Walk to the shop and show the code to collect their prints

The chemist's computer has a physical printer connected via USB.
A lightweight Node.js agent runs silently in the background on 
that computer. The moment a job is paid, the agent detects it, 
downloads the file, and sends it directly to the printer.
The chemist does not need to touch the computer for printing to happen.

This feature must feel like a standalone mini-app within the 
existing Diamond Chemist platform — same design language, same 
navigation, but its own dedicated section.

