  {print_job_id}/{original_filename_sanitized}
  Example: a3f9c2d1-1234/prescription_scan.pdf

The file is only accessible via a signed URL generated 
server-side by the Edge Function, valid for 60 seconds.
The signed URL is never exposed to the customer frontend —
only to the authenticated print agent.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────
EDGE FUNCTIONS — build all 5
─────────────────────────────────────────────────

1. create-print-job
   Trigger: Customer submits the print order form
   Input:   { customer_name, customer_phone, file_path, 
              file_name, file_type, page_count, copies, 
              colour_mode, sides, paper_size }
   Logic:
     a. Validate all fields server-side
     b. Fetch price from print_pricing table for these settings
     c. Calculate total: price_per_page × page_count × copies
        (double-sided halves the page count billed)
     d. Generate pickup code: "PRN-" + 4 random uppercase 
        alphanumeric chars (check uniqueness in DB)
     e. Create Razorpay order server-side with total_amount
     f. Insert row into print_jobs with status PENDING_PAYMENT
     g. Return { job_id, pickup_code, razorpay_order_id, 
                 razorpay_key_id, total_amount }
   Security:
     - Encrypt customer_phone with AES-256 before DB insert
     - Rate limit: max 3 print jobs per phone per hour
     - Validate file path exists in Supabase Storage
     - Validate page_count is not 0 or negative
     - Validate copies is between 1 and 50

2. verify-print-payment
   Trigger: Razorpay payment success callback on frontend
   Input:   { job_id, razorpay_order_id, 
              razorpay_payment_id, razorpay_signature }
   Logic:
     a. Verify Razorpay signature using HMAC-SHA256
        (razorpay_order_id + "|" + razorpay_payment_id 
         signed with RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET)
     b. If signature invalid → return 400, do NOT update DB
     c. If valid → update print_jobs:
          status = 'PAID'
          paid_at = now()
          razorpay_payment_id = verified payment id
     d. Send SMS via MSG91:
        "Hi {name}! Your print job is confirmed. 
         Pickup code: {code}. We'll SMS you when ready. 
         - Diamond Chemist"
     e. Return { success: true }
   Critical: NEVER mark as PAID without signature verification.

3. agent-poll
   Trigger: Print agent polls every 5 seconds
   Auth:    Requires AGENT_SECRET header (a long random string 
            set as env variable, known only to the agent script)
   Input:   { agent_version }
   Logic:
     a. Verify AGENT_SECRET header
     b. SELECT top 5 rows WHERE status = 'PAID' 
        ORDER BY paid_at ASC (oldest first, FIFO queue)
     c. For each job, generate a signed download URL 
        (60-second expiry) for the file in Storage
     d. Return array of job objects with signed URLs
   Security:
     - If AGENT_SECRET missing or wrong → 401
     - Signed URLs expire in 60s so intercepted URLs 
       are useless

4. agent-update-status
   Trigger: Print agent reports job completion or failure
   Auth:    Same AGENT_SECRET header
   Input:   { job_id, status, error_log? }
             status can be 'PRINTING' | 'READY' | 'ERROR'
   Logic:
     a. Verify AGENT_SECRET
     b. Update print_jobs row
     c. If status = 'READY':
          Send SMS: "Your prints are ready at Diamond Chemist! 
          Show code {code} to collect. Open till 10PM."
     d. If status = 'ERROR':
          Send SMS to customer: "Sorry, your print job 
          failed. Please contact the shop. Full refund 
          will be processed. Code: {code}"
          Alert admin via a special SMS too
     e. Return { success: true }

5. collect-print-job
   Trigger: Admin scans/enters pickup code at counter
   Auth:    Requires valid Supabase JWT (admin logged in)
   Input:   { pickup_code }
   Logic:
     a. Find job by pickup_code
     b. Verify status is 'READY' (if not, return error with 
        current status so admin can explain to customer)
     c. Update status = 'COLLECTED', collected_at = now()
     d. Return full job details for admin to verify

─────────────────────────────────────────────────
THE PRINT AGENT — local Node.js script
─────────────────────────────────────────────────

This is a separate file: agent/print-agent.js
The chemist runs this once on their computer and it runs 
silently in the background forever.

Tech stack for agent:
  node-printer     (sends files to Windows/Linux print queues)
  pdf-to-printer   (wrapper for PDF direct printing)
  mammoth          (converts DOCX to PDF before printing)
  sharp            (normalises image files before printing)
  node-fetch       (polls Edge Functions)
  dotenv           (loads SUPABASE_URL, AGENT_SECRET, 
                    PRINTER_NAME from .env file)

Agent logic (pseudo-code):

  async function pollAndPrint() {
    
    // 1. Fetch PAID jobs from server
    const jobs = await fetch(EDGE_URL/agent-poll, {
      headers: { 'x-agent-secret': AGENT_SECRET }
    })
    
    for (const job of jobs) {
      
      // 2. Mark as PRINTING immediately 
      //    (prevents other agents printing same job)
      await updateStatus(job.id, 'PRINTING')
      
      // 3. Download file using signed URL
      const fileBuffer = await downloadFile(job.signed_url)
      
      // 4. Convert if needed
      if (job.file_type === 'docx') {
        fileBuffer = await convertDocxToPdf(fileBuffer)
      }
      if (job.file_type === 'image') {
        fileBuffer = await convertImageToPdf(fileBuffer, {
          paper_size: job.paper_size
        })
      }
      
      // 5. Build print options
      const printOptions = {
        printer: PRINTER_NAME,
        copies:  job.copies,
        sides:   job.sides === 'double' ? 'two-sided-long-edge' : 'one-sided',
        colorModel: job.colour_mode === 'colour' ? 'color' : 'gray',
        paperSize: job.paper_size.toUpperCase(),
      }
      
      // 6. Send to printer
      await printFile(fileBuffer, printOptions)
      
      // 7. Update status to READY
      await updateStatus(job.id, 'READY')
      
      // 8. Delete file from local temp storage
      cleanupTempFile()
    }
  }
  
  // Poll every 5 seconds
  setInterval(pollAndPrint, 5000)
  console.log('Diamond Chemist Print Agent running...')
  console.log('Watching for new print jobs...')

Agent startup script for Windows (agent/start-agent.bat):
  @echo off
  echo Starting Diamond Chemist Print Agent...
  node print-agent.js
  pause

