PART 5 — EDGE CASES & ERROR HANDLING
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Every one of these must be explicitly handled:

UPLOAD ERRORS:
  File too large (>25MB) → inline error on drop zone
  Unsupported format     → inline error on drop zone
  Network error during upload → retry button, keep form state
  Storage bucket full    → "Service temporarily unavailable"

PAYMENT ERRORS:
  Razorpay modal closed without paying:
    Do NOT create the print job in DB
    Do NOT upload to final path
    Show: "Payment cancelled. Your file is still saved. 
           Try again?" with a "Retry Payment" button
  
  Payment succeeds but signature verification fails:
    Show: "Payment verification failed. Do not attempt again.
           Contact Diamond Chemist with reference: {razorpay_payment_id}"
    Log the discrepancy for admin review
  
  Payment succeeds but Edge Function crashes:
    Razorpay webhook as fallback — 
    configure webhook in Razorpay dashboard to hit 
    /verify-print-payment as a POST with the event data.
    This ensures no payment is lost even if the user 
    closes their browser.

PRINT AGENT ERRORS:
  Agent offline when job is PAID:
    Jobs queue in DB with status PAID
    Agent processes them in order when it reconnects
    Customer is NOT notified of delay immediately
    If status stays PAID for > 15 minutes:
      Edge Function (cron job every 10 mins) sends SMS:
      "Your print job is queued. We'll start printing shortly."
  
  Printer paper jam / error during printing:
    Agent catches the printer error
    Calls agent-update-status with status=ERROR, 
    error_log = printer error message
    Customer gets SMS about failure
    Admin gets alert SMS
    Refund must be processed manually via Razorpay dashboard
    (Document this in the admin guide)
  
  DOCX conversion fails:
    mammoth conversion error → agent reports ERROR
    Customer notified, refund issued

FILE ISSUES:
  Corrupted PDF:
    Agent detects during print → ERROR status
  
  Password-protected PDF:
    Agent cannot print → ERROR status
    Customer SMS: "Your PDF appears to be password-protected.
    Please upload an unlocked version."
  
  Extremely large page count (200+ pages):
    Edge Function caps at 200 pages
    Show warning: "Large document detected (200+ pages).
    This may take several minutes to print."

