PART 6 — SECURITY REQUIREMENTS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

1. File access:
   Files in Supabase Storage are PRIVATE.
   Never generate a public URL for any uploaded file.
   Only the print agent can access files via 
   short-lived signed URLs from Edge Functions.
   Admin can download via authenticated Edge Function.

2. Pickup code security:
   Codes are random, not sequential.
   "PRN-0001, PRN-0002" is guessable — never do this.
   4-char alphanumeric = 1.6 million combinations.
   After 3 failed code attempts from same IP in 
   10 minutes, rate-limit further attempts.

3. Price integrity:
   Total amount is ALWAYS calculated server-side 
   in create-print-job Edge Function.
   Frontend price display is for UX only.
   The Razorpay order amount comes from the server.
   A user cannot manipulate the price in DevTools.

4. File retention:
   Print files are automatically deleted from 
   Supabase Storage 48 hours after job is COLLECTED 
   or CANCELLED. (Use a Supabase cron job or 
   pg_cron scheduled function.)
   Do not store customer documents longer than needed.
   Document this in the privacy policy.

5. Phone number encryption:
   Same AES-256 pattern as medicine orders.
   PII_ENCRYPTION_KEY env variable.
   Decrypted only in get-orders (admin) and 
   when sending SMS via MSG91.

