PART 7 — MICRO-INTERACTIONS & POLISH
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

These are non-negotiable for a professional product:

1. File drop zone: 
   Smooth border-color + bg-color transition (200ms) 
   on drag-enter and drag-leave.

2. Upload progress:
   Real progress bar tracking Supabase Storage upload 
   percentage (use the onUploadProgress callback).
   Not a fake progress bar.

3. Price calculator:
   Every change to settings triggers an instant 
   re-calculation with a brief 150ms CSS transition 
   on the total amount (scale: 1.05 → 1.0).

4. Step progress bar:
   Smooth width transition (300ms ease) when advancing 
   to the next step.

5. Pickup code reveal:
   On the success screen, the code characters appear 
   one by one with a 80ms stagger delay — like a 
   combination lock settling into place.

6. Status tracker:
   When a status step completes, the circle fills 
   with a smooth 400ms fill animation.
   The connecting line between steps fills 
   left-to-right.

7. "Mark Collected" button:
   Requires a 2-second press-and-hold (show a 
   progress fill on the button itself) to prevent 
   accidental taps. 
   This is critical — once marked collected, 
   it cannot be undone.

8. Copy code button:
   Instant visual feedback: icon changes from 
   ti-copy to ti-check, text changes to "Copied!",
   reverts after 2 seconds.

9. Agent status dot:
   The green "online" dot pulses gently (CSS keyframe 
   opacity 1 → 0.4 → 1, 2s infinite) to show it's 
   alive, not frozen.

10. Print job card in admin:
    "PRINTING NOW" status card has a subtle 
    horizontal shimmer animation across it 
    (like a progress bar sweeping) to indicate 
    active work. NOT a full skeleton loader — 
    just a 3px shimmer line at the top of the card.

